    "I. INTRODUCTIONLiterature reviews have gained considerable importance for scholars.",
    "It provides researchers with a comprehensive overview of previous findings in a specific field and assists scholars in identifying gaps in past understandings.",
    "It helps to conduct future research and informs researchers of areas where they can provide significant input.",
    "However, conducting literature reviews can be incredibly cumbersome because there's so much to read.",
    "Due to the vast volume of research articles being released, reviewing all related studies and extracting relevant information can be a time-consuming, tedious, and error-prone task."
